<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1827,2034]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,150,358]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1827,1853]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Type data:</emphasis>
In the original description 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[593,745,1827,1853]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref21677" refString="Friese, H. (1899) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned “one specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1234,1827,1853]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(St. Parime); one female at 
<collectionCode box="[263,329,1863,1889]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
”. It is not clear if he was talking about two females, one of them without provenance label or only a single female from 
<collectingCountry box="[392,507,1899,1925]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
housed in that collection. Apparently, the second option is the right, because a female from that country with original Friese’s label was found in that collection. If my interpretation is correct, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveofasciata">
<emphasis box="[1411,1430,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,300,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">niveofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single specimen (
<typeStatus box="[751,852,1971,1998]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
) and not from a type series as interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="114 - 123" refId="ref22477" refString="Moure, J. S. (1969) Notas sobre algumas especies de Centris da Guiana (Hym., Apoidea). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 41 (1), 114 - 123." type="journal article" year="1969">Moure (1969)</bibRefCitation>
who designated that specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[666,772,2007,2033]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[837,935,2007,2033]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[1281,1396,2007,2033]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
St. Parime 1897 [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Fr." authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[415,693,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveofasciata">
<emphasis box="[415,654,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">Centris niveofasciata</emphasis>
Fr.
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[701,722,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] 1910 Friese det. [printed]\ Coll. Friese [printed]\ [red label] Type [printed] (
<collectionCode box="[449,515,187,213]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
